<!-- ===================================================================
     FAQ
     =================================================================== -->
<section id="faq" class="stripe faq">
  <div class="wrap" style="display:grid;grid-template-columns:1fr 1.3fr;gap:60px;align-items:start;">
    <div class="reveal">
      <p class="eyebrow">FAQ</p>
      <h2 class="h2">Common<br/>questions.</h2>
      <p class="body-lg" style="margin-top:18px;max-width:280px;">Don't see yours? <a href="mailto:hi@attic.it.com">Email us.</a> We answer everything personally.</p>
    </div>
    <div class="faq__grid reveal" data-delay="1">
      <details>
        <summary>What if I need something immediately?</summary>
        <p>Same- or next-day delivery is included — schedule a return in the app and we'll bring your bin back on the next available window. No rush fees.</p>
      </details>
      <details>
        <summary>How do you keep my things safe?</summary>
        <p>Every bin is tagged with a QR code and scanned at every handoff — pickup, arrival at the facility, shelf placement, and return — so there's a full custody trail. Storage is climate-controlled at 65–72°F. Contents are insured up to $2,000 per bin.</p>
      </details>
      <details>
        <summary>Can I send bins back if I don't need them anymore?</summary>
        <p>Yes, any time. If a bin is empty at your home, tap "Send it back" in the app and we'll retrieve it at no cost. Your monthly fee for that bin stops at the next billing cycle.</p>
      </details>
      <details>
        <summary>What counts as a "bin"?</summary>
        <p>A standard 27-gallon heavy-duty tote, about the size of a large moving box — 29×18×15 inches. We provide them; you don't need to supply your own containers.</p>
      </details>
      <details>
        <summary>How much stuff fits in a bin?</summary>
        <p>Roughly: an entire holiday decor setup, a season of clothes for two adults, or about 20 college-sized textbooks with room for a few keepsakes.</p>
      </details>
      <details>
        <summary>Do you have a minimum?</summary>
        <p>Nope. Start with one bin, finish with fifty. We don't care — we just want to be useful.</p>
      </details>
      <details>
        <summary>How do I get started?</summary>
        <p>We're opening Attic to Denver residents in small batches. <a href="#waitlist">Request an invite</a> and we'll send a code as spots open up — usually within a week.</p>
      </details>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

